author: COMSOL
description: This example simulates atmospheric corrosion of a galvanic couple, comprising of an aluminum alloy and steel, which is in contact with electrolyte film of 50 micrometer thickness. The model presented here accounts for charge transport as well mass transport involving 10 species and 6 homogeneous reactions. The model computes the transient and spatial distribution of species in the film, including the corrosion products.
label: atmospheric_corrosion_mass_transport.mph
